DTSTAMP:20260327T021230Z
DTSTART:20260330T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, March 30\, 2026\, 10am - 6pm\n\nThis exhibit highlight
	s the diversity and depth of The Seattle Public Library's collection\, com
	posed of over two million items.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nR
	oom Location: Level 8 - Gallery\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is 
	not required.\n\nDetailed Description: Enjoy viewing books\, ephemera\, ar
	t\, and more at our exhibit in the Level 8 Gallery between January 23\, 20
	26 and April 11\, 2026.\, Thanks to our sponsor\n\nThe Seattle Public Libr
	ary Foundation .\n\nEvent Logistics:\n\nFind out about Exhibits.\n\nContac
	t Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-38
	6-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people wi
	th disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven
	 days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs a
	re free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#
	/details/collection-spotlight-exhibit/18084351/2026-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAto
	day - Arts & Culture
